ce of wealth"},{"d":"विपुलाम्","m":"huge"},{"d":"श्रियम्","m":"wealth"},{"d":"इच्छताम्","m":"desire"},{"d":"तेषाम्","m":"their"},{"d":"अभिहितम्","m":"advice"},{"d":"वचः","m":"words"},{"d":"न कार्यम्","m":"not to be followed."}]},{"v":16,"dev":"अहितं च हिताकारंधार्ष्ट्याज्जल्पन्तियेनराः ।अवेक्ष्यमन्त्रबाह्यास्तेकर्तव्याःकृत्यदूषणा:।। 6.63.16।।","trans":"\"Those who tender advice, which is unwholesome but in wholesome grab, out of their impudence should be kept away from discussion examining early as they mar the purpose.\"","words":[{"d":"ये","m":"those"},{"d":"नराः","m":"people"},{"d":"हिताकारम्","m":"in wholesome grab"},{"d":"अहितम्","m":"not good"},{"d":"धार्ष्ट्यात्","m":"out of impudence"},{"d":"जल्पन्ति","m":"prattle"},{"d":"कृत्यदूषणा:","m":"mar the purpose"},{"d":"ते","m":"they"},{"d":"अवेक्ष्य","m":"examining early"},{"d":"मन्त्रबाह्याः","m":"keep them away from discussion"},{"d":"कर्तव्याः","m":"is essential duty."}]},{"v":17,"dev":"विनाशयन्तोभर्तारंसहिताश्शत्रुभिर्बुधैः ।विपरीतानिकृत्यानिकारयन्तीहमन्त्रिणः","trans":"\"Some ministers in order to ruin the king, collide with enemies and make the king take wrong actions.\"","words":[{"d":"इह","m":"some"},{"d":"मन्त्रिणः","m":"ministers"},{"d":"भर्तारम्","m":"king's"},{"d":"विनाशयन्तः","m":"to ruin"},{"d":"शत्रुभिः","m":"enemies"},{"d":"सहिताः","m":"collide"},{"d":"विपरीतानि","m":"wrong"},{"d":"कृत्यानि","m":"actions"},{"d":"कारयन्ति","m":"will undertake."}]},{"v":18,"dev":"तान्भर्तामित्रसङ्काशानमित्रान्मन्त्रनिर्णये ।व्यवहारेणजानीयात्सचिवानुपसम्हितान्","trans":"\" A ruler should know those ministers bribed by the enemy, who have become close to the enemy and appear as friends. Those ministers must be known through their behaviour in the deliberations.\"","words":[{"d":"भर्ता","m":"ruler"},{"d":"उपसम्हितान्","m":"who have become close to enemy"},{"d":"मित्रसङ्काशान्","m":"appearing as friends"},{"d":"अमित्रान्","m":"enemies"},{"d":"तान्","m":"they"},{"d":"सचिवान्","m":"ministers"},{"d":"मन्त्रनिर्णये","m":"through their behaviour"},{"d":"व्यवहारेण","m":"in deliberations"},{"d":"जानीयात्","m":"must know."}]},{"v":19,"dev":"चपलस्येहकृत्यानिसहसानुप्रधावतः ।छिद्रमन्येप्रपद्यन्तेक्रौञ्चस्य ख मिवद्विजाः","trans":"\"Enemies find out the weakness of the king who is unsteady and rush after the actions forcibly without thinking like brahmins just as birds find the holes in Krauncha mountain and elaborate to others.\"","words":[{"d":"चपलस्य","m":"unsteady"},{"d":"कृत्यानि","m":"actions"},{"d":"सहसा","m":"forcibly"},{"d":"अनुप्रधावतः","m":"rush after"},{"d":"छिद्रम्","m":"containing holes"},{"d":"क्रौञ्चस्य","m":"Krauncha mountain"},{"d":"खम्","m":"birds"},{"d":"द्विजाःइव","m":"like brahmins"},{"d":"अन्ये","m":"other"},{"d":"प्रपद्यन्ते","m":"elaborate."}]},{"v":20,"dev":"योहिशत्रुमवज्ञायनात्मानमभिरक्षति ।अवाप्नोतिहिसोऽनर्थान् स्थानाच्चव्यवरोप्यते","trans":"\"He who knowing fully the actions of the enemy does not protect himself he attains reverses and is also dragged down from position.\"","words":[{"d":"यः","m":"he who"},{"d":"शत्रुम्","m":"enemy"},{"d":"अवज्ञाय","m":"knowing fully"},{"d":"आत्मानम्","m":"himself"},{"d":"नाभिरक्षति","m":"does not protect himself"},{"d":"सः","m":"he"},{"d":"अनर्थान्","m":"reverses"},{"d":"अवाप्नोतिहि","m":"attains"},{"d":"स्थानात्","m":"from position"},{"d":"व्यवरोप्यते च","m":"is dragged"}]},{"v":21,"dev":"यदुक्तमिहतेपूर्वंक्रियतामनुजेन च ।तदेवनोहितंवाक्यंयदिच्छसि च तत्कुरु","trans":"\"The advice given to you in the past by your brother alone is good. That is good for you. Or you may do what you wish.\"","words":[{"d":"पूर्वम्","m":"in the past"},{"d":"ते","m":"you"},{"d":"अनुजेन","m":"brother's"},{"d":"यत्","m":"that which"},{"d":"उक्तम्","m":"was told"},{"d":"क्रियताम्","m":"do that"},{"d":"नः","m":"not"},{"d":"तत्","m":"that"},{"d":"वाक्यमेव","m":"that advice alone"},{"d":"हितम्","m":"is good"},{"d":"यत्","m":"that"},{"d":"इच्छसि","m":"you wish"},{"d":"तत्","m":"that"},{"d":"कुरु","m":"you may do."}]},{"v":22,"dev":"तत्तुश्रुत्वादशग्रीवःकुम्भकर्ण